		<description><![CDATA[If you were to count up the hundreds of—thousands of—random acts of kindness and genuine care for each other, the likes of which I witnessed firsthand ten years ago today, if you took each of those moments and strung them together like bulbs on a line, they’d shine like a beacon in the dark and [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.honeyhelpyourself.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Towers.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1584" title="Towers" src="http://www.honeyhelpyourself.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Towers-241x300.jpg" alt="" width="241" height="300" /></a></p>
<p>If you were to count up the hundreds of—<em>thousands</em> of—random acts of kindness and genuine care for each other, the likes of which I witnessed firsthand ten years ago today, if you took each of those moments and strung them together like bulbs on a line, they’d shine like a beacon in the dark and make for a safer passage through.</p>
